long_desc.thetext:
Your package openttd failed to build from source in current rawhide.
https://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=17746734
For details on mass rebuild see https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_26_Mass_Rebuild

This package is affected by multiple issues, all of them related to "config.lib".
Another hidden issue without effects when building in chroots. is libtimidity's pkg-config *.pc, which adds a bogus -L to linker calls.
This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 26 development cycle. Changing version to '26'.

(In reply to Ralf Corsepius from comment #4) > Another hidden issue without effects when building in chroots. is > libtimidity's pkg-config *.pc, which adds a bogus -L to linker calls.
This particular issue has recently been fixed in mainstream libtimidity v0.2.4 release. (cf. bug #1426676)
